{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19691.The_Hunt_for_Red_October", "title": "The Hunt for Red October", "titleComplete": "The Hunt for Red October (Jack Ryan, #3)", "description": "Here is the runaway bestseller that launched Tom Clancy's phenomenal career. A military thriller so gripping in its action and so convincing in its accuracy that the author was rumored to have been debriefed by the White House. Its theme: the greatest espionage coup in history. Its story: the chase for a top secret Russian missile sub. Lauded by the Washington Post as \"breathlessly exciting.\" The Hunt for Red October remains a masterpiece of military fiction by one of the world's most popular authors, a man whose shockingly realistic scenarios continue to hold us in thrall.Somewhere under the Atlantic, a Soviet sub commander has just made a fateful decision. The Red October is heading west. The Americans want her. The Russians want her back. And the most incredible chase in history is on...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1281995542i/19691.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Espionage", "Suspense", "Military Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Fiction", "War", "Mystery", "Action", "Thriller"], "asin": "0425172902", "isbn": "0425172902", "isbn13": "9780425172902", "publisher": "Berkley Trade", "series": ["Jack Ryan Universe (Publication Order)", "Jack Ryan Universe", "Jack Ryan"], "author": ["Tom Clancy"], "publishDate": 939970800000, "characters": ["Oliver Wendell Tyler", "Alexei Arbatov", "Dr. Cathy Ryan", "Marko Aleksandrovich Ramius", "Ivan Yurievich Putin", "Charles Davenport", "Ronald Jones", "Viktor Alexievich Tupolev", "Bartolomeo Vito Mancuso", "Jack Ryan Sr*", "Valintin Bugayev"], "places": ["Atlantic Ocean", "London, England", "Moscow", "Washington, D.C."], "ratingHistogram": [10472, 15792, 59697, 124914, 162865], "ratingsCount": 373740, "reviewsCount": 4060, "numPages": 432, "language": "English"}
