{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/184591.The_Innocence_of_Father_Brown", "title": "The Innocence of Father Brown", "titleComplete": "The Innocence of Father Brown (Father Brown, #1)", "description": "Chesterton portrays Father Brown as a short, stumpy Roman Catholic priest, with shapeless clothes and a large umbrella, and an uncanny insight into human evil. \"How in Tartarus,\" cried Flambeau, \"did you ever hear of the spiked bracelet?\" -- \"Oh, one's little flock, you know!\" said Father Brown, arching his eyebrows rather blankly. \"When I was a curate in Hartlepool, there were three of them with spiked bracelets.\" Not long after he published Orthodoxy, G. K. Chesterton moved from London to Beaconsfield, and met Father O'Connor. O'Connor had a shrewd insight to the darker side of man's nature and a mild appearance to go with it--and together those came together to become Chesterton's unassuming Father Brown. Chesterton loved the character, and the magazines he wrote for loved the stories. The Innocence of Father Brown was the first collection of them, and it's a great lot of fun.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388284048i/184591.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Detective", "Christian", "Fiction", "Short Stories", "British Literature", "Classics", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Crime"], "asin": "0809592533", "isbn": "0809592533", "isbn13": "9780809592531", "publisher": "Wildside Press", "series": ["Father Brown"], "author": ["G.K. Chesterton"], "publishDate": 1078128000000, "characters": ["Aristide Valentin", "Hercule Flambeau", "Father Brown"], "places": ["United Kingdom"], "ratingHistogram": [312, 1134, 4548, 6220, 4678], "ratingsCount": 16892, "reviewsCount": 1392, "numPages": 232, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/43673.The_First_Deadly_Sin", "title": "The First Deadly Sin", "titleComplete": "The First Deadly Sin (Deadly Sins, #2)", "description": "New York Police Department Captain Edward Delaney is called to the scene of a brutal murder. A Brooklyn councilman was struck from behind, the back of his skull punctured and crushed with an unknown weapon. The victim wasn\u2019t robbed, and there\u2019s no known motive. The commissioner appoints Delaney to head up a clandestine task force, but soon this effort ignites an internecine war of departmental backstabbing. Distracted by the serious illness of his wife, Barbara, Delaney begins his secret investigation. Then the killer claims another victim\u2014slain in the exact same way, leaving the strange puncture wound. As more young men are found murdered, Delaney starts putting the pieces together. Soon, he\u2019s faced with a cop\u2019s dilemma: He knows who the killer is, but the man is untouchable. That\u2019s when Delaney lays a trap to bring a monster to justice . . .", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1348147968i/43673.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Detective", "Suspense", "Fiction", "Mystery Thriller", "Classics", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Psychological Thriller", "Crime"], "asin": "B002J3M7WK", "isbn": "0425104273", "isbn13": "9780425104279", "publisher": "PENGUIN PUTNAM * TRADE", "series": ["Deadly Sins"], "author": ["Lawrence Sanders"], "publishDate": 315561600000, "ratingHistogram": [161, 370, 1818, 3614, 3515], "ratingsCount": 9478, "reviewsCount": 268, "numPages": 628, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18999.Smiley_s_People", "title": "Smiley's People", "titleComplete": "Smiley's People (George Smiley, #7; Karla Trilogy, #3)", "description": "John le Carre's classic novels deftly navigate readers through the intricate shadow worlds of international espionage with unsurpassed skill and knowledge and have earned him -- and his hero, British Secret Service agent George Smiley -- unprecedented worldwide acclaim.Rounding off his astonishing vision of a clandestine world, master storyteller le Carre perfects his art in Smiley's People. In London at dead of night, George Smiley, sometime acting Chief of the Circus (aka the British Secret Service), is summoned from his lonely bed by news of the murder of an ex-agent. Lured back to active service, Smiley skillfully maneuvers his people -- the no-men of no-man's land -- into crisscrossing Paris, London, Germany, and Switzerland as he prepares for his own final, inevitable duel on the Berlin border with his Soviet counterpart and archenemy, Karla.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1348407722i/18999.jpg", "genres": ["Espionage", "Novels", "Suspense", "Historical Fiction", "Fiction", "Spy Thriller", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Crime"], "asin": "0743455800", "isbn": "0743455800", "isbn13": "9780743455800", "publisher": "Scribner", "series": ["George Smiley", "The Karla Trilogy"], "author": ["John le Carr\u00e9"], "publishDate": 1038297600000, "characters": ["Peter Guillam", "Connie Sachs", "Toby Esterhase", "George Smiley", "Oliver Lacon"], "places": ["Berlin"], "ratingHistogram": [348, 791, 5058, 14069, 18507], "ratingsCount": 38773, "reviewsCount": 1275, "numPages": 397, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Los Angeles Times Book Prize", "awardedAt": 315561600000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
