{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30005.Red_Harvest", "title": "Red Harvest", "titleComplete": "Red Harvest (The Continental Op #1)", "description": "When the last honest citizen of Poisonville was murdered, the Continental Op stayed on to punish the guilty\u2014even if that meant taking on an entire town. The Op was in Personville, derogatory nickname aside, as the result of a letter to the Continental Detective Agency in San Francisco from Donald Willsson, publisher of the local paper, asking for an agent to visit. No other information. As soon as the OP arrives, the body count begins and it starts with his client! \"Red Harvest\" is more than a superb crime novel; it is a classic exploration of corruption and violence in America and one of the greats of 20th century literature.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1320423692i/30005.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Detective", "Noir", "Fiction", "Hard Boiled", "Classics", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Crime"], "asin": "0752852612", "isbn": "0752852612", "isbn13": "9780752852614", "publisher": "UNSPECIFIED VENDOR", "series": ["The Continental Op"], "author": ["Dashiell Hammett"], "publishDate": 1041408000000, "characters": ["Dan Rolff", "Al Kennedy", "Polly de Voto", "Police Chief John Noonan", "The corpse at Elihu's house", "The Mayor and the Governor", "Men working for Whisper", "Ike Bush", "Tony Agosti", "Bob MacSwain", "Charles Proctor Dawn", "Bill Quint", "Max \"Whisper\" Thaler", "Senator Keefer", "Lew Yard", "Ricker, a guy with a hire heap", "Reno Starkey", "The Old Man (The Continental Op)", "The Continental Op", "Mrs. Donald Willsson", "Dinah Brand", "Donald Willsson", "Elihu Willsson", "Helen Albury", "Peak Murry", "Tim Noonan", "Lillian Gish (Red Harvest)", "Robert Albury at First National", "Keever the house cop, and the manager", "The warehouse security guard", "Pete the Finn", "Tommy Robins", "J. W. Clark", "Miss Lewis