{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/86658.The_Secret_Agent", "title": "The Secret Agent", "titleComplete": "The Secret Agent", "description": "Mr Verloc, the secret agent, keeps a shop in London's Soho where he lives with his wife Winnie, her infirm mother, and her idiot brother, Stevie. When Verloc is reluctantly involved in an anarchist plot to blow up the Greenwich Observatory things go disastrously wrong, and what appears to be \"a simple tale\" proves to involve politicians, policemen, foreign diplomats, and London's fashionable society in the darkest and most surprising interrelations.Based on the text which Conrad's first English readers enjoyed, this new edition includes a full and up-to-date bibliography, a comprehensive chronology and a critical introduction which describes Conrad's great London novel as the realization of a \"monstrous town,\" a place of idiocy, madness, criminality, and savage butchery. It also discusses contemporary anarchist activity in the UK, imperialism, and Conrad's narrative techniques.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1171075859i/86658.jpg", "genres": ["Espionage", "Literature", "Novels", "Fiction", "British Literature", "Classics", "Mystery", "Thriller", "20th Century", "Crime"], "asin": "0192801694", "isbn": "0192801694", "isbn13": "9780192801692", "publisher": "Oxford University Press", "author": ["Joseph Conrad", "John Lyon"], "publishDate": 1083222000000, "characters": ["the Assistant Commissioner", "Mr. Vladimir", "Winnie Verloc", "Karl Yundt", "Adolf Verloc", "Chief Inspector Heat", "Michaelis", "Sir Ethelred", "Comrade Alexander Ossipon", "Stevie"], "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [691, 2202, 7219, 8055, 4436], "ratingsCount": 22603, "reviewsCount": 1733, "numPages": 304, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2247142.The_Talented_Mr_Ripley", "title": "The Talented Mr. Ripley", "titleComplete": "The Talented Mr. Ripley (Ripley, #1)", "description": "Since his debut in 1955, Tom Ripley has evolved into the ultimate bad boy sociopath, influencing countless novelists and filmmakers. In this first novel, we are introduced to suave, handsome Tom Ripley: a young striver, newly arrived in the heady world of Manhattan in the 1950s. A product of a broken home, branded a \"sissy\" by his dismissive Aunt Dottie, Ripley becomes enamored of the moneyed world of his new friend, Dickie Greenleaf. This fondness turns obsessive when Ripley is sent to Italy to bring back his libertine pal but grows enraged by Dickie's ambivalent feelings for Marge, a charming American dilettante. A dark reworking of Henry James's The Ambassadors, The Talented Mr. Ripley\u2014is up to his tricks in a '90s film and also Rene Clement's '60s film, Purple Noon.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1634841836i/2247142.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Suspense", "Noir", "Fiction", "Italy", "Classics", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Crime"], "asin": "0393332144", "isbn": "0393332144", "isbn13": "9780393332148", "publisher": "W. W. Norton  Company", "series": ["Ripley"], "author": ["Patricia Highsmith"], "publishDate": 1213686000000, "characters": ["Tom Ripley", "Marge Sherwood", "Freddie Miles", "Dickie Greenleaf"], "places": ["New York City, New York", "Italian Riviera", "Venice", "Italy", "Mongibello", "Rome"], "ratingHistogram": [1514, 4161, 18869, 38115, 26299], "ratingsCount": 88958, "reviewsCount": 5988, "numPages": 273, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Grand Prix de Litt\u00e9rature Polici\u00e8re", "awardedAt": -410198400000, "category": "Romans \u00e9trangers", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Edgar Award", "awardedAt": -441820800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
