{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22034.The_Godfather", "title": "The Godfather", "titleComplete": "The Godfather (The Godfather, #1)", "description": "The Godfather\u2014the epic tale of crime and betrayal that became a global phenomenon.Almost fifty years ago, a classic was born. A searing portrayal of the Mafia underworld, The Godfather introduced readers to the first family of American crime fiction, the Corleones, and their powerful legacy of tradition, blood, and honor. The seduction of power, the pitfalls of greed, and the allegiance to family\u2014these are the themes that have resonated with millions of readers around the world and made The Godfather the definitive novel of the violent subculture that, steeped in intrigue and controversy, remains indelibly etched in our collective consciousness.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1394988109i/22034.jpg", "genres": ["Literature", "Novels", "Drama", "Historical Fiction", "Fiction", "American", "Classics", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Crime"], "publisher": "NAL", "series": ["Mario Puzo's Mafia", "The Godfather"], "author": ["Robert Thompson", "Peter Bart", "Mario Puzo"], "publishDate": 1014969600000, "characters": ["Constanzia \"Connie\" Corleone", "Tom Hagen", "Peter \"Pete\" Clemenza", "Johnny Fontane", "Santino \"Sonny\" Corleone", "Michael \"Mike\" Corleone", "Al Neri", "Don Vito Corleone", "Rocco Lampone", "Fredo \"Freddie\" Corleone", "Luca Brasi"], "places": ["Sicily", "The United States of America", "New York (State)"], "ratingHistogram": [5189, 9216, 42176, 123079, 238271], "ratingsCount": 417931, "reviewsCount": 12648, "numPages": 448, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/92364.Eye_of_the_Needle", "title": "Eye of the Needle", "titleComplete": "Eye of the Needle", "description": "One enemy spy knows the secret to the Allies' greatest deception, a brilliant aristocrat and ruthless assassin -- code name: \"The Needle\" -- who holds the key to ultimate Nazi victory. Only one person stands in his way: a lonely Englishwoman on an isolated island, who is beginning to love the killer who has mysteriously entered her life. All will come to a terrifying conclusion in Ken Follett's unsurpassed and unforgettable masterwork of suspense, intrigue, and the dangerous machinations of the human heart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327939511i/92364.jpg", "genres": ["Espionage", "Thriller", "Suspense", "Historical", "Fiction", "War", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Historical Fiction", "World War II"], "asin": "006074815X", "isbn": "006074815X", "isbn13": "9780060748159", "publisher": "William Morrow Paperbacks", "author": ["Ken Follett"], "publishDate": 1072944000000, "characters": ["Henry Faber", "Lucy Rose"], "places": ["United Kingdom", "England", "British Isles"], "ratingHistogram": [1254, 3410, 23797, 61250, 66213], "ratingsCount": 155924, "reviewsCount": 4075, "numPages": 368, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Edgar Award", "awardedAt": 284025600000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17245.Dracula", "title": "Dracula", "titleComplete": "Dracula", "description": "You can find an alternative cover edition for this ISBN here and here.When Jonathan Harker visits Transylvania to help Count Dracula with the purchase of a London house, he makes a series of horrific discoveries about his client. Soon afterwards, various bizarre incidents unfold in England: an apparently unmanned ship is wrecked off the coast of Whitby; a young woman discovers strange puncture marks on her neck; and the inmate of a lunatic asylum raves about the 'Master' and his imminent arrival.In Dracula, Bram Stoker created one of the great masterpieces of the horror genre, brilliantly evoking a nightmare world of vampires and vampire hunters and also illuminating the dark corners of Victorian sexuality and desire.This Norton Critical Edition includes a rich selection of background and source materials in three areas: Contexts includes probable inspirations for Dracula in the earlier works of James Malcolm Rymer and Emily Gerard. Also included are a discussion of Stoker's working notes for the novel and \"Dracula's Guest,\" the original opening chapter to Dracula. Reviews and Reactions reprints five early reviews of the novel. \"Dramatic and Film Variations\" focuses on theater and film adaptations of Dracula, two indications of the novel's unwavering appeal. David J. Skal, Gregory A. Waller, and Nina Auerbach offer their varied perspectives. Checklists of both dramatic and film adaptations are included.Criticism collects seven theoretical interpretations of Dracula by Phyllis A. Roth, Carol A. Senf, Franco Moretti, Christopher Craft, Bram Dijkstra, Stephen D. Arata, and Talia Schaffer.A Chronology and a Selected Bibliography are included.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1387151694i/17245.jpg", "genres": ["Paranormal", "Literature", "19th Century", "Novels", "Vampires", "Fiction", "Fantasy", "Horror", "Classics", "Gothic"], "asin": "0393970124", "isbn": "0393970124", "isbn13": "9780393970128", "publisher": "Norton", "author": ["David J. Skal", "Bram Stoker", "Rub\u00e9n Toledo", "Nina Auerbach"], "publishDate": 516265200000, "characters": ["Quincey P. Morris", "Thomas Bilder", "Mr. Swales", "Petrof Skinsky", "Braithwaite Lowrey", "John Rawlings", "George Canon", "John Paxton", "Andrew Woodhouse", "Jonathan Harker", "Abraham Van Helsing", "Arthur Holmwood", "Mrs. Tom", "Petrofsky", "Olgaren", "Sister Agatha", "Mr. Carter", "Lucy Westenra", "Mina Harker", "Arminus", "Dracula", "Lord Godalming", "Rufus Smith", "R.M. Renfield", "J. M. Caffyn", "John Seward", "Peter Hawkins", "Bersicker", "Samuel F. Billington", "Patrick Hennessey, M. D., M. R. C. S. L. K. Q. C. P. I., etc., etc.,"], "ratingHistogram": [23134, 63449, 260084, 445542, 473850], "ratingsCount": 1266059, "reviewsCount": 45591, "numPages": 488, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/153492.The_39_Steps", "title": "The 39 Steps", "titleComplete": "The 39 Steps (Richard Hannay, #1)", "description": "Adventurer Richard Hannay, just returned from South Africa, is thoroughly bored with London life\u2014until he is accosted by a mysterious American, who warns him of an assassination plot that could completely destabalise the fragile political balance of Europe. Initially sceptical, Hannay nonetheless harbours the man\u2014but one day returns home to find him murdered... An obvious suspect, Hannay flees to his native Scotland, pursued by both the police and a cunning, ruthless enemy. His life and the security of Britain are in grave peril, and everything rests on the solution to a baffling enigma: what are the 'thirty nine steps?'", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1391320797i/153492.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Espionage", "Historical Fiction", "Fiction", "Scotland", "Classics", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Crime"], "asin": "1419151126", "isbn": "1419151126", "isbn13": "9781419151125", "publisher": "William Blackwood & Sons", "series": ["Richard Hannay"], "author": ["John Buchan"], "publishDate": 1087455600000, "characters": ["Richard Hannay", "Walter Bullivant"], "places": ["Scotland", "London, England", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [1091, 3999, 13532, 14597, 8467], "ratingsCount": 41686, "reviewsCount": 3466, "numPages": 100, "language": "English"}
